1
00:00:43,439 --> 00:00:44,240
Don't tell me

2
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:47,960
you still don't trust these shiny silver coins?

3
00:00:49,159 --> 00:00:49,439
This...

4
00:00:49,439 --> 00:00:50,520
They're really paying real money!

5
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:50,799
This one...

6
00:00:50,799 --> 00:00:51,719
This is real money!

7
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:54,840
Just bring the girls over here

8
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,439
and get paid silver dollars on the spot.

9
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:00,039
Looks like this deal is legit!

10
00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:01,880
Mayor, wait here for a moment.

11
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:03,560
I'll go get my daughter right now.

12
00:01:03,759 --> 00:01:04,799
Me too, me too!

13
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:05,719
Slow down!

14
00:01:05,879 --> 00:01:06,560
Slow down!

15
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,079
Brother-in-law,

16
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:13,879
money really makes ghosts push mills, huh?

17
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,799
I don't know if it makes ghosts push mills,

18
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:19,840
but getting a back rub? Sure can.

19
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,920
Look at you, every day dressed up

20
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,359
all flashy and gaudy,

21
00:01:30,359 --> 00:01:31,719
like some big butterfly.

22
00:01:31,719 --> 00:01:33,319
You fly off and never come back.

23
00:01:33,319 --> 00:01:35,439
Grocery shopping until past midnight.

24
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:37,079
Are you trying to starve me to death?

25
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,280
What's wrong?

26
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:40,480
You missed me just from a grocery run?

27
00:01:41,359 --> 00:01:42,000
I missed...

28
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:42,719
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

29
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,120
Look at you,

30
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:46,760
flirting with an old geezer every day.

31
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,799
Is that fun for you?

32
00:01:48,159 --> 00:01:49,200
It is fun.

33
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,640
Let me show you something even more fun.

34
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:54,280
I'm not looking, I'm hungry.

35
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,959
No looking, no eating.

36
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:00,640
What is this?

37
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,760
Why didn't our Xiaolian catch this chance?

38
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:08,319
We scrimped and saved to send her to school,

39
00:02:08,319 --> 00:02:09,800
and now they're handing out money!

40
00:02:11,439 --> 00:02:11,919
Something's not right.

41
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,439
What's not right?

42
00:02:15,879 --> 00:02:17,000
It's a scam.

43
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:18,919
How could it be?

44
00:02:18,919 --> 00:02:20,759
The Mayor himself handed it out.

45
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:22,120
Over a dozen kids went,

46
00:02:22,159 --> 00:02:23,560
over a dozen kids signed up.

47
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:28,599
Don't you know foreigners used high pay

48
00:02:28,599 --> 00:02:29,719
to trick so many women back then?

49
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,960
Then what happened?

50
00:02:31,879 --> 00:02:32,319
Half of them

51
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:33,680
were sold to brothels.

52
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,360
The other half

53
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,919
were sold off to Southeast Asia as slaves.

54
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,800
So what do we do?

55
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:40,800
I'll go house to house and warn them.

56
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,879
Go on, go, go.

57
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,599
See how many families will believe you.

58
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,719
Why wouldn't they believe me?

59
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:48,080
They've already taken the silver coins.

60
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:48,879
Will they believe you?

61
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,240
Then think of something.

62
00:02:51,039 --> 00:02:52,319
They're our neighbors.

63
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,560
I can't think of anything.

64
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:54,759
I've got heartburn already.

65
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:56,879
Have some scallions.

66
00:02:56,879 --> 00:02:57,240
Eat.

67
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:57,840
Go on, eat.

68
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,360
Eat!

69
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:02,280
Are you even human?

70
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,280
So what if they're our neighbors?

71
00:03:04,479 --> 00:03:05,080
Sis,

72
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,879
stop making trouble here.

73
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,639
The Brigade Commander said if it works,

74
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:12,039
he'll back him for County Magistrate.

75
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,520
Then you'll be the Magistrate's wife.

76
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,800
And maybe

77
00:03:16,159 --> 00:03:18,159
I could even get to be Mayor myself.

78
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:20,879
This is completely immoral!

79
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,560
There will be karma!

80
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:25,000
Stop yapping.

81
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,360
What karma?

82
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,319
Aren't I doing just fine right now?

83
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:29,159
Where's the karma?

84
00:03:30,319 --> 00:03:31,199
Hasn't it hit yet?

85
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:34,400
Our Qiuying was buried alive!

86
00:03:34,719 --> 00:03:36,039
Isn't that karma?

87
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:37,639
Shut your mouth!

88
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,879
Hey, you,

89
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:40,479
talk some sense into your sister.

90
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:44,400
Sis,

91
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,400
how about

92
00:03:46,639 --> 00:03:47,439
you get some rest.

93
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:49,159
Don't bring up sore subjects.

94
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:49,840
Alright?

95
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:50,479
Go to bed.

96
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:55,240
Just keep asking for trouble.

97
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:03,199
How many do we have now?

98
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:05,759
Sixteen in total.

99
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,280
Still too few.

100
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:09,879
Here's what you do.

101
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,400
Starting tomorrow,

102
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,479
take the four-year-olds too.

103
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:17,240
County Magistrate,

104
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,120
Brilliant!

105
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,680
Suck-up.

106
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,560
You little Mayor.

107
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,040
Keep up back there.

108
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,240
Boss,

109
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,680
you've tied this way too tight.

110
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:36,439
How about loosening it for me?

111
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,079
You talk too much.

112
00:04:38,959 --> 00:04:39,800
Keep your mouth shut.

113
00:04:39,959 --> 00:04:41,279
Why such a temper?

114
00:04:41,279 --> 00:04:42,560
I was just saying.

115
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,120
Boss,

116
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:51,800
is that gun real or just to scare kids?

117
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:54,759
Want to find out?

118
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,759
No, no, no!

119
00:04:55,839 --> 00:04:56,439
Boss, boss,

120
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:57,720
calm down, calm down.

121
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,199
I was just joking.

122
00:05:00,519 --> 00:05:01,560
Quit the nonsense.

123
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,759
All of you, stop crying!

124
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,920
What's there to cry about?

125
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:13,319
I'm taking you to the city girls' school.

126
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:14,720
What an honor that is.

127
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,319
No more crying.

128
00:05:16,319 --> 00:05:17,000
You hear me?

129
00:05:18,399 --> 00:05:20,040
Boss, you're lying, aren't you?

130
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,920
Who goes to school with their hands tied?

131
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,920
You really won't shut up, huh?

132
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:28,360
I tied you up

133
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:32,040
because it's a dark road at night

134
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:32,920
and I was afraid you'd get lost.

135
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,079
Let me tell you one more thing.

136
00:05:35,759 --> 00:05:36,839
In these mountains,

137
00:05:37,839 --> 00:05:39,759
there's a Fox Immortal Lady.

138
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,959
She eats little kids just like you.

139
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:44,439
So you,

140
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:46,959
better not bring her here.

141
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:47,839
You hear me?

142
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,399
Who's looking for me?

143
00:05:51,439 --> 00:05:52,160
See?

144
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,399
Look,

145
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,680
she's here, isn't she?

146
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:55,720
Who?

147
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:58,079
It's her!

148
00:07:15,279 --> 00:07:16,199
Stay back!

149
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,160
Stay back!

150
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,319
Stay back!

151
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,000
Don't come any closer!

152
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,160
Idiot.

153
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,120
Useless trash.

154
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,120
Can't even handle a simple task.

155
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,480
Brigade Commander,

156
00:07:35,519 --> 00:07:36,759
the Fox Immortal Lady is real.

157
00:07:37,199 --> 00:07:38,079
Last night,

158
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,439
her head was this big,

159
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:40,120
she...

160
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:41,920
she chased me all night long!

161
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,800
So many people there,

162
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,160
why did she chase only you?

163
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:52,160
Just because you're handsome?

164
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:55,920
Qiuying.

165
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:57,720
It was Qiuying.

166
00:07:58,639 --> 00:07:59,079
Brigade Commander,

167
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,360
Qiuying is the Fox Immortal Lady.

168
00:08:00,399 --> 00:08:00,959
Qiuying.

169
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:02,600
Brother-in-law.

170
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,319
Qiuying, Qiuying.

171
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,680
And who's Qiuying?

172
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,160
Brigade Commander,

173
00:08:08,199 --> 00:08:09,560
Great men have short memories.

174
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:10,879
Qiuying

175
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,439
is my daughter.

176
00:08:13,079 --> 00:08:14,360
The one who was buried

177
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,959
together with your son.

178
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,759
My poor daughter.

179
00:08:18,759 --> 00:08:19,279
Hold your tears.

180
00:08:20,279 --> 00:08:20,920
Qiuying.

181
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:23,959
Mystic Lady,

182
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:24,439
is...

183
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:25,759
is all of this

184
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:27,480
really true?

185
00:08:30,759 --> 00:08:32,399
You two, come with me.

186
00:08:35,519 --> 00:08:35,879
Brother-in-law.

187
00:08:35,879 --> 00:08:36,799
I'll go, Brigade Commander.

188
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:37,960
Brother-in-law.

189
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:38,799
I'm not going.

190
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:39,519
Brother-in-law!

191
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,240
Get lost!

192
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,240
Qiuying.

193
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,600
Dig.

194
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:00,759
Master.

195
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,080
Are you sure you want to dig?

196
00:09:02,639 --> 00:09:03,080
Dig.

197
00:09:04,799 --> 00:09:06,399
Dig, dig, dig!

198
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:12,679
Open the coffin.

199
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,720
Qiuying isn't dead.

200
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,360
Qiuying isn't dead!

201
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:21,879
Sis.

202
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,240
It's not that she didn't die.

203
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:24,960
She became the Fox Immortal Lady.

204
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:27,000
Brother-in-law, what do we do?

205
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:29,159
How should I know?

206
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:31,600
Master.

207
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,720
My daughter couldn't have...

208
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,600
really turned into the Fox Immortal Lady?

209
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:06,720
Shopkeeper Wang, what's going on?

210
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:08,480
What else could it be?

211
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,679
He's just a coffin seller.

212
00:10:10,159 --> 00:10:12,159
At worst, he sold a defective one.

213
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,639
A defective coffin?

214
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,279
Could a dead person run out of the coffin?

215
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,759
Both of you, shut up!

216
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:19,399
Stop talking nonsense.

217
00:10:21,799 --> 00:10:22,360
Shopkeeper Wang.

218
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,159
After you.

219
00:10:39,799 --> 00:10:41,480
I heard Dongsheng and the Brigade Commander

220
00:10:41,879 --> 00:10:43,200
went off to fight again.

221
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,519
He's just a foot soldier.

222
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:45,559
What else would he do but fight?

223
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,240
Lao Jiugui.

224
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,360
My left eyelid's been twitching lately.

225
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:56,440
I feel something big is about to happen.

226
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:59,320
When Dongsheng is back, don't let him go.

227
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,360
You're getting older too.

228
00:11:01,519 --> 00:11:03,039
Just let him stay here at Jigu Temple.

229
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,480
Alright.

230
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,440
I'll do as you say.

231
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:07,840
Following that Brigade Commander

232
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,480
won't end well for him.

233
00:11:12,399 --> 00:11:13,919
Seize Lao Jiugui!

234
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:19,679
Lord Beile's all dressed up so slick,

235
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,200
out bullying common folk again.

236
00:11:22,679 --> 00:11:23,879
I never bully common folk.

237
00:11:24,279 --> 00:11:25,240
I only bully you.

238
00:11:25,399 --> 00:11:26,639
What right do you have to arrest him?

239
00:11:26,799 --> 00:11:28,120
This has nothing to do with you.

240
00:11:28,519 --> 00:11:29,399
You'd better stay out of it.

241
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:30,639
After you.

242
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,840
I'll go with him.

243
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:35,399
It's nothing big.

244
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:37,799
Let's go.

245
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:40,200
Put it down.

246
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,480
It's not that big a deal.

247
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:42,279
Take him away.

248
00:11:55,519 --> 00:11:56,320
Shopkeeper Wang.

249
00:12:02,279 --> 00:12:04,320
Lao Jiugui, you don't know how I suffered.

250
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,559
I never gave you up.

251
00:12:05,879 --> 00:12:07,720
But they used some kind of dark sorcery,

252
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,120
and I confessed everything.

253
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:11,840
You've suffered.

254
00:12:18,399 --> 00:12:20,480
They probably didn't even hit you.

255
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,960
Lao Jiugui, I'll walk myself.

256
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:26,600
I'll do it myself.

257
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:27,559
Shopkeeper Wang.

258
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,919
I don't blame you for selling me out.

259
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,720
Our friendship still stands.

260
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:37,799
Lord Beile.

261
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:40,440
I take full responsibility for my actions.

262
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,080
Let Shopkeeper Wang go.

263
00:12:47,679 --> 00:12:49,000
Let Shopkeeper Wang go!

264
00:12:49,879 --> 00:12:51,200
You know what I'm capable of.

265
00:12:53,679 --> 00:12:54,200
Release him.

266
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:56,000
Release him now.

267
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,399
Shopkeeper Wang.

268
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:03,919
Go home.

269
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,919
Pick out a suitable one for me.

270
00:13:06,799 --> 00:13:08,039
Of course, a double-layered one.

271
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:15,639
That's thoughtful of you.

272
00:13:18,679 --> 00:13:19,840
Fellow townspeople,

273
00:13:20,639 --> 00:13:21,639
I have an announcement.

274
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,039
One year ago,

275
00:13:23,039 --> 00:13:25,879
Lao Jiugui freed two Communist bandits.

276
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,799
Convicted of Crime of Communist Collusion.

277
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:30,480
Today, beheading and public display,

278
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:31,919
to be carried out immediately.

279
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:33,600
Execute him.

280
00:13:40,879 --> 00:13:41,440
Kneel down.

281
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,000
I have one request.

282
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,279
Make it quick for me.
